A team agreement was created to define working norms, responsibilities, and collaboration rules for the development of CookSnap â€“ 
Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images. This agreement ensures smooth teamwork, accountability, and effective communication throughout the project lifecycle.

Team Working Norms
All team members will actively participate in project-related activities.
Tasks will be distributed equally among team members based on assigned roles.
Regular discussions will be conducted to track project progress.
All major decisions will be made collectively by the team.
Any issues or conflicts will be resolved through mutual discussion.

Communication Guidelines
Team members will communicate through regular meetings and online collaboration platforms.
Important updates, changes, and milestones will be shared with all members.
Project deadlines will be strictly followed.
Quality and Responsibility Agreement
Each team member is responsible for completing assigned tasks on time.
Work submitted by any member will be reviewed by at least one other team member.

The team agrees to maintain academic integrity, originality, and ethical standards.

This team agreement was accepted by all members to ensure disciplined, collaborative, and efficient execution of the CookSnap project.
